# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — RUST CROSSES TO 76 +
#                                                  AXIS 21 (TEMPLATING ENGINES) OPENS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# the 76TH Rust CLI library variant.  Rust climbs from 75 to 76
# documented libraries (tera via ragit).  Rust **breaks the three-way
# tie** at 75 and goes SOLO at 76 (Rust=76, Go=75, TS-Node=75).  New
# leaderboard: Rust=76, Go=75, TypeScript-Node=75 (Rust solo at the top).
# Taxonomy now spans 405 cross-language CLI library variants across
# 100 documented languages (POST-100-LANGUAGE-MILESTONE).
#
# Pattern: R669 Rust=75 (serde_yaml → Axis 20 OPENS) → R670 Go=75
# (yaml.v3) → R671 TS-Node=75 (js-yaml → Axis 20 1/1/1) → R672 100TH
# LANGUAGE (Cpp2 / cppfront) → R673 Rust=76 (tera THIS — AXIS 21
# OPENS) → expected R674 Go=76 → R675 TS-Node=76 → R676 101ST
# LANGUAGE.  This is the 1st of 3 leader bumps in the post-100-
# language-milestone segment.
#
# This completion OPENS Axis 21 (TEMPLATING ENGINES) — the 21st
# documented cross-language CLI library axis.  Axis 21 covers the
# cross-language pattern of "library used by CLIs to render text
# templates with variable interpolation, control flow, and
# composition" — applicable to project scaffolding tools (cookiecutter,
# yeoman, cargo-generate), static site generators (Hugo, Jekyll,
# Zola, Eleventy), code generators (openapi-generator, gqlgen),
# email templating, configuration templating (Jinja2-style ansible),
# and LLM prompt templates (this CLI's primary use case).
#
#   Axis 21 (TEMPLATING ENGINES) variants:
#     - tera (Keats/tera) — R673 (THIS) — Rust Jinja2/Django-
#       inspired templating; runtime-compiled; inheritance +
#       includes; ~60 built-in filters; custom filters/tests/
#       functions; Vincent Prouillet / Keats ecosystem
#     - (Go variant pending in R674 — likely text/template +
#       html/template stdlib OR Pongo2 (Django-style) OR templ
#       (a-h/templ, typed Go templates))
#     - (TS-Node variant pending in R675 — likely handlebars
#       (most popular Mustache-style) OR nunjucks (Jinja2 in
#       Node, by Mozilla) OR ejs)
#
# Axis 21 distribution: Rust=1, Go=0, TS-Node=0.  Will reach 1/1/1
# three-language symmetry by end of R675.
#
# Cross-language Axis 21 design analysis:
#   The "template engine" abstraction is partially stdlib in some
#   languages — Go ships text/template + html/template in its
#   standard library (basic Mustache-like with Go-specific
#   actions).  Rust + Node both require third-party libraries.
#   Even where Go has stdlib templates, most production code uses
#   alternatives (Pongo2 for Django-style, templ for typed
#   templates) because text/template is rudimentary.  Axis 21
#   thus has TWO competing design philosophies:
#     - Mustache family (handlebars, mustache): logic-less
#     - Jinja2 family (tera, nunjucks, Twig, Liquid): full
#       expressions + filters + inheritance
#   Each variant in our taxonomy represents one of these
#   philosophies.
#
# Axis distribution summary after R673:
#   * Axis 1  (Argparse):     Rust=N  / Go=N  / TS-Node=N
#   * Axis 4  (Colors):       Rust=N  / Go=N  / TS-Node=N
#   * Axis 5  (Progress):     Rust=N  / Go=N  / TS-Node=N
#   * Axis 6  (Errors):       Rust=6  / Go=N  / TS-Node=N
#   * Axis 7  (Boxes):        Rust=1  / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 8  (Prompts):      Rust=1  / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 9  (Logging):      Rust=6  / Go=6  / TS-Node=6   (6/6/6)
#   * Axis 10 (Tables):       Rust=2  / Go=2  / TS-Node=2   (2/2/2)
#   * Axis 11 (Humanization): Rust=1  / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 12 (Text Wrap):    Rust=1  / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 13 (Config Files): Rust=2  / Go=2  / TS-Node=2   (2/2/2)
#   * Axis 14 (Paths):        Rust=2  / Go=2  / TS-Node=2   (2/2/2)
#   * Axis 15 (Date/Time):    Rust=1  / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 16 (HTTP Clients): Rust=1  / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 17 (File Watching): Rust=1 / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 18 (WebSockets):    Rust=1 / Go=1  / TS-Node=1   (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 19 (Markdown Parsing): Rust=1 / Go=1 / TS-Node=1 (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 20 (YAML Parsing):     Rust=1 / Go=1 / TS-Node=1 (1/1/1)
#   * Axis 21 (Templating Engines): Rust=1 / Go=0 / TS-Node=0 NEW
#
# Vincent Prouillet / Keats ecosystem note:
#   Vincent Prouillet (Keats on GitHub) is a French Rust
#   developer maintaining a full Rust static-site / templating
#   stack:
#     * tera          — Jinja2/Django templates                  (THIS)
#     * zola          — static site generator (uses tera)
